\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3.1}{\ignorespaces CA-DQStream Architecture Overview. Raw taxi records flow through four validation layers: Schema Checker, Hard Rules, Context-Aware Rules, and ML Layer. Each layer emits violations to dedicated Kafka topics. Quality meta-streams (aggregated metrics) are fed to ADWIN for drift detection, triggering self-adaptation when baselines become stale.}}{1}{figure.caption.14}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:architecture_overview}{{3.1}{1}{CA-DQStream Architecture Overview. Raw taxi records flow through four validation layers: Schema Checker, Hard Rules, Context-Aware Rules, and ML Layer. Each layer emits violations to dedicated Kafka topics. Quality meta-streams (aggregated metrics) are fed to ADWIN for drift detection, triggering self-adaptation when baselines become stale}{figure.caption.14}{}}
